      <section eId="sec_CCP-4463">
        <num>CCP 4463</num>
        <heading>4463. Â Tutor without bond; undertutor</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-4463__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court may dispense with the furnishing of security by a legal tutor appointed in a proceeding under this Chapter.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-4463__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the court is satisfied that no one will accept the dative tutorship of a minor in a proceeding under this Chapter and furnish the usual security, if required, it shall appoint a dative tutor, who shall comply with all requirements except that of furnishing security.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-4463__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court may dispense with the appointment of an undertutor in a proceeding under this Chapter.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111996</p>
        </authorialNote>
